text: "Identify the part of the cochlear implant marked?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Grounding electrode", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "Amplifier", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Receiver", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Electrode array", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "In a cochlear implant, the grounding electrode is an extracochlear electrode placed outside the cochlea (often in temporalis muscle or subperiosteal region) to complete the electrical circuit.<br><br>\u00b7\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Electrode array: Inserted into cochlea \u2192 stimulates auditory nerve\n\u00b7\u00a0 \u00a0 Receiver-stimulator: Implanted under the skin \u2192 receives signals from external device\n\u00b7\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Grounding electrode: Provides reference/return path for electrical current<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/229f6291-88c6-4ec8-ae16-ed367fe2b20e.png\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
