explanation: "K\u00f6rner\u2019s septum (petrosquamous lamina) is a bony plate that may persist in the temporal bone and can obscure access to the mastoid antrum during mastoid surgery.<br><br>**Clinical significance:**<br><br>* Can make mastoid antrum difficult to locate\n* Risk of incomplete mastoidectomy\n* Important surgical landmark in otologic surgery",
