explanation: "Congenital anomalies of the pinna are classified based on size, shape, and developmental defects of auricular cartilage.<br><br>Correct associations:<br><br>* Microtia: Abnormally small or rudimentary pinna\n* Bat ear (prominent ear): Underdeveloped/absent antihelix \u2192 protruding ear\n* Mozart ear: Fusion of helix and antihelix (loss of normal folds)\n* Wildermuth ear: Small, rudimentary ear with poorly formed cartilage (not large)",
